# Master Data Import

## Config-Driven Approach
All 6 master types defined in `MASTER_CONFIGS` dict. Each has: `sheet`, `table`, `columns` mapping, `pk`, `dedup` field.

## MySQL Tables

| Table | Primary Key | Key Lookup Fields |
|---|---|---|
| `customer_master` | internal_id | old_code → internal_id, code, customer_name |
| `item_master` | internal_id | old_item_code → internal_id, item_code |
| `location_master` | location_id | plant → location_id, location_name |
| `payment_term_master` | internal_id | payment_term_code → internal_id, name |
| `sales_rep_master` | internal_id | first_name_th + last_name_th (fuzzy), employee_id, name |
| `shipping_label_master` | address_internal_id | address_label (fuzzy), ship_to_code |

## Import Behavior
- Creates database if not exists
- Truncates table before insert (if exists)
- Sets primary key on first creation
- Drops duplicates on dedup field before insert
